# Implement URL Content Fetching Functionality

## Background

We are developing a content aggregation platform. One of its core features is to generate a content preview for URLs entered by users, similar to the title and summary displayed when sharing links on social media. To achieve this, we need a backend service that can accept a URL, then use the OkHttp library to fetch the HTML content of the webpage corresponding to that URL.

## Requirements

Please implement the `fetchUrlContent(String url)` method. This method should take a string-type URL as a parameter, use an OkHttp client to send a GET request to that URL, and return the retrieved HTML page content as a string. If any IO error occurs during the request, the method should directly throw an `IOException`.

## Tech Stack

["Java8+", "OkHttp"]

## Implementation Requirements

- Package name: `com.example.service`
- Class name: `WebContentService`
- Method signature: `public String fetchUrlContent(String url) throws IOException`
- Implementation requirement: Please use an `okhttp3.OkHttpClient` instance to create and execute the request. Specifically, prepare the network call by invoking the `newCall(request)` method.
- Appropriate exception handling is required
- Code should be concise and efficient
- No security vulnerabilities


